"title": "5854: experience, of God",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5854",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Scripture stresses the importance and also the possibility of a true experience of the living God. This is contrasted with the more academic knowledge about him. Experiential knowledge of God comes through personal encounter, through the witness of the Holy Spirit, through reflection on his past goodness and through the shared experiences of others.</p>\n<h2>Personal experience of God</h2>\n<h3>Contrasted with academic knowledge</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job42:5\">JOB 42:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:34\">JER 31:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:42\">JHN 4:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:39-John5:40\">JHN 5:39–5:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:19\">JAS 2:19</a></p>\n<h3>Experience of God's blessing</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps34:8\">PSA 34:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:3\">1PE 2:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb6:4-Heb6:5\">HEB 6:4–6:5</a></p>\n<h3>Experiencing God through Scripture</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:29\">MAT 22:29</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:39-John5:40\">JHN 5:39–5:40</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:11-Acts17:12\">ACT 17:11–17:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim3:15-2Tim3:17\">2TI 3:15–3:17</a></p>\n<h3>Knowing God through the Spirit</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:15-Rom8:16\">ROM 8:15–8:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:16-John14:17\">JHN 14:16–14:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:26\">JHN 14:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:14-John16:15\">JHN 16:14–16:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor2:9-1Cor2:10\">1CO 2:9–2:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa64:4\">ISA 64:4</a></p>\n<h3>Examples of personal encounter with God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut11:2-Deut11:7\">DEU 11:2–11:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:3-Deut5:4\">DEU 5:3–5:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen32:30\">GEN 32:30</a> <em>Jacob</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:3-Exod3:4\">EXO 3:3–3:4</a> <em>Moses</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:1\">ISA 6:1</a> <em>Isaiah</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:3-Acts9:6\">ACT 9:3–9:6</a> <em>Saul of Tarsus</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor12:2-2Cor12:4\">2CO 12:2–12:4</a> <em>Paul</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:17\">REV 1:17</a> <em>John</em></p>\n<h2>Sharing experience of God</h2>\n<h3>Experience of God through his people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech8:23\">ZEC 8:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa45:14\">ISA 45:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:24-1Cor14:25\">1CO 14:24–14:25</a></p>\n<h3>Leaders with experience of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh24:31\">JOS 24:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num12:8\">NUM 12:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:22\">JDG 6:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:21-Acts1:22\">ACT 1:21–1:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:3-1Cor15:7\">1CO 15:3–15:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet1:16-2Pet1:18\">2PE 1:16–1:18</a></p>\n<h3>Speaking to future generations</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut4:9-Deut4:10\">DEU 4:9–4:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod10:2\">EXO 10:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:20-Deut6:21\">DEU 6:20–6:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job8:8-Job8:9\">JOB 8:8–8:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps71:18\">PSA 71:18</a></p>\n<h3>Speaking from personal experience: OT</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:18-Deut7:19\">DEU 7:18–7:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam17:34-1Sam17:37\">1SA 17:34–17:37</a> <em>David's experience teaches him to trust God.</em><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa43:14-Isa43:17\">ISA 43:14–43:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa51:9-Isa51:11\">ISA 51:9–51:11</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer16:14-Jer16:15\">JER 16:14–16:15</a></p>\n<h3>Speaking from personal experience: NT</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:11\">JHN 3:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:18\">JHN 20:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:13\">ACT 4:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John1:1-1John1:3\">1JN 1:1–1:3</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John9:25\">JHN 9:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark5:19-Mark5:20\">MRK 5:19–5:20</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:39\">LUK 8:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:28-John4:29\">JHN 4:28–4:29</a></p>\n<h2>Confidence based on past experience</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:9-Matt16:10\">MAT 16:9–16:10</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:18-Mark8:20\">MRK 8:18–8:20</a> <em>The disciples' experience of Jesus Christ's provision should have taught them not to worry about food</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:17-2Tim4:18\">2TI 4:17–4:18</a></p>",
